-- Emirates Will Become Men’s Tennis Tour’s Official Airline
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-12-27T10:52:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-27/emirates-will-become-men-s-tennis-tour-s-official-airline.html
Emirates, the world’s biggest
airline by international traffic, will become the official
carrier of the men’s tennis tour for the next five years, both
parties said today.  The Dubai-based airline will also sponsor the ATP tennis
rankings starting Jan. 1, the ATP World Tour said in a
statement on its website today. The rankings are currently
sponsored by  South African Airways .  “We’re delighted to welcome Emirates as the official
airline of the ATP World Tour,” Brad Drewett, ATP executive
chairman and president, said in the statement. “It’s fantastic
news for men’s professional tennis that a brand of Emirates’
global stature has pledged their support to the ATP World Tour
for the next five years.”  Emirates sponsor several ATP World Tour Masters 1000 events
and the  U.S. Open  Series and are also an official partner of the
U.S. Open.  Today’s announcement “is a perfect addition to our
existing portfolio of global sports sponsorships,” Emirates
executive vice chairman Maurice Flanagan said in an e-mailed
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
